- consider you are using 2 virtual host but actually you are using 1 virtual box
- ensure that sshd service should run always, even if reboot as well.

- create user admin1 and admin2 and set password as 1234
- create sshkeys from admin1 user and push the keys to admin2 user
- try to login to admin2 user from admin1 user
- try to copy files from admin1 user to admin2 user 
- now open a new terminal login as admin2 user 
- try to login from admin2 user to user1

- list out the files present in admin1 and admin2user ~/.ssh/ folder

- explore scp and rsync command 
